-ran: '/challenge/victim'
-flag popped out

## 🧑🏾‍🏫 what this challenge teaches u
.bashrc is a configuration file that executes commands every time a shell session is launched.
it's possible to modify another users .bashrc file by appending a command at the end and when the user opens a new shell, the command is executed automatically

